Minister of Basic Education Angie Motshekga is Mzansi’s
acting president for the weekend. President Cyril Ramaphosa is on his way to Japan to watch
the Springboks’ Rugby World Cup final match against England on Saturday. According to SowetanLIVE, Ramaphosa deputy, David Mabuza, is
in China, chairing talks between the two governments. In a statement on Thursday, presidency spokesperson Khusela
Diko said Ramaphosa will leave today for Yokohama, to lead the nation’s support
for the Springboks. “The President will lend his support to the Springboks and
supporters of the national team in terms of his constitutionally assigned role
of 'promoting the unity of the nation and that which will advance the Republic',”
said Diko in the statement. Minister of Basic Education Angie Motshekga is Mzansi’s
